<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00374</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING ARTICLES 96 AND 124 OF THE FAMILY CODE OF THE PHILIPPINES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Removes the portion in Articles 96 and 124 of the Family Code which gives preference to the husband's decision over that of the wife in case of disagreement on the administration and enjoyment of the conjugal or community property; preserves and safeguards from unilateral and reckless decisions that are often resorted to when conflict occurs between wife and husband. (Extracted from Explanatory Note) </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BROSAS, ARLENE D., DE JESUS, EMMI A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Zarate (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>2. Elago (007 2016-08-08)</td><tr><td>3. Castro (F.L.) (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>4. Casilao (007 2016-08-08)</td><tr><td>5. Tinio (007 2016-08-08)</td><td>6. Panotes (021 2016-09-13)</td><tr><td>7. Roa-Puno (091 2017-05-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Committee Report filed on 2017-02-07</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-House Committee Report No. 138 substituted by HB No. 5156 (in substitution of HB Nos. 219, 374, 375, 1159, 2386 & 3263</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp2. Scheduled for meeting/hearing on 2017-02-13</b><tr><td colspan=3>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp-continuation of consideration of similar bills (HB Nos. 00219, 00374, 00375,01159, 02386, 03263 and 03951)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp